I was having problems with my Raspberry Pi 2 and my bluetooth speaker because when I tried to use it to play music it kept wanting to reconnect to something else. After a bit of searching I found that it was using the Pulse Audio daemon. Even after running “pactl load-module module-bluetooth-disconnect=no” it still kept trying to connect over and over again.

I found out that I had to run “pactl unload-module module-bluetooth-policy”. After logging out and back in again, I finally managed to disable the bluetooth daemon at boot so I do not have to keep typing this command at the start of every time I want to use the bluetooth speaker.
